Commentary Text: Nortje to Kedar Jadhav, out Lbw!! Kedar has been given OUT LBW, that looks so plumb, but he still wants a review, is there an inside edge? Only that can save him here. Doesn't looks like, Ultraedge confirms a flat line. Impact in front of off and crashing into middle of middle. Not sure what prompted Kedar into reviewing this one, has cost his team their inly review as well. Pitched up and angling back into the right-hander, Kedar shuffled right across on the flick and once he missed, there was only one way he was heading to. easy call for the umpire and the Sunrisers have lost half their side. Kedar Jadhav lbw b Nortje 3(8)

Commentary Text: Khaleel Ahmed to Prithvi Shaw, out Caught by Williamson!! That's a superb catch by Williamson! Khaleel is excited as his skipper has taken an impressive catch. Quite a romantic moment that. Shaw has thrown away his wicket in his quest to be too aggressive. Was a slower length delivery around off and Prithvi hoicks it across the line. Doesn't get the timing or connection right. And Williamson runs towards his right from mid-on and completes a well judged sliding catch. Gavaskar on air compares it to the catch taken by Kapil Dev during the 1983 World Cup final. Prithvi Shaw c Williamson b Khaleel Ahmed 11(8) [4s-2]
